## Clearance from wall cabinets ##

Clearance from wall cabinets refers to the space needed between appliances or countertops and overhead cabinets to ensure safety and usability. For example, cooktops typically require 18â€“24 inches of clearance below wall cabinets, while microwaves or vent hoods need sufficient space above for ventilation. Adequate clearance prevents heat damage, allows comfortable movement, and maintains workflow efficiency.